  96 def compare_dates(d1, d2):
  97     try:
  98         date1 = parse_isodate(d1, allow_date=True)
  99         date2 = parse_isodate(d2, allow_date=True)
 100         return date1 == date2
 101     except ValueError:
 102         # At least one of d1 and d2 cannot be parsed. Simply compare values.
 103         return d1 == d2

 106 class ReporterEncoder(json.JSONEncoder):
 107     def default(self, o):
 108         if isinstance(o, Exception):
 109             return str(o)
 110 
 111         return json.JSONEncoder.default(self, o)
 112 
 113 
 114 class Reporter:
 115     def __init__(self):
 116         self.files = OrderedDict()
 117 
 118     def _ensure_default_entry(self, path):
 119         try:
 120             self.files[path]
 121         except KeyError:
 122             self.files[path] = {
 123                 'errors': [],
 124                 'warnings': [],
 125                 'traces': [],
 126                 'warning_traces': []
 127             }
 128 
 129     def _log(self, path, code, msg, level='error', line=0, column=0):
 130         self._ensure_default_entry(path)
 131         lvl_dct = self.files[path]['%ss' % level]
 132         lvl_dct.append({
 133             'code': code,
 134             'msg': msg,
 135             'line': line,
 136             'column': column
 137         })
 138 
 139     def error(self, *args, **kwargs):
 140         self._log(*args, level='error', **kwargs)
 141 
 142     def warning(self, *args, **kwargs):
 143         self._log(*args, level='warning', **kwargs)
 144 
 145     def trace(self, path, tracebk):
 146         self._ensure_default_entry(path)
 147         self.files[path]['traces'].append(tracebk)
 148 
 149     def warning_trace(self, path, tracebk):
 150         self._ensure_default_entry(path)
 151         self.files[path]['warning_traces'].append(tracebk)
 152 
 153     @staticmethod
 154     @contextmanager
 155     def _output_handle(output):
 156         if output != '-':
 157             handle = open(output, 'w+')
 158         else:
 159             handle = sys.stdout
 160 
 161         yield handle
 162 
 163         handle.flush()
 164         handle.close()
 165 
 166     @staticmethod
 167     def _filter_out_ok(reports):
 168         temp_reports = OrderedDict()
 169         for path, report in reports.items():
 170             if report['errors'] or report['warnings']:
 171                 temp_reports[path] = report
 172 
 173         return temp_reports
 174 
 175     def plain(self, warnings=False, output='-'):
 176         """Print out the test results in plain format
 177 
 178         output is ignored here for now
 179         """
 180         ret = []
 181 
 182         for path, report in Reporter._filter_out_ok(self.files).items():
 183             traces = report['traces'][:]
 184             if warnings and report['warnings']:
 185                 traces.extend(report['warning_traces'])
 186 
 187             for trace in traces:
 188                 print('TRACE:')
 189                 print('\n    '.join(('    %s' % trace).splitlines()))
 190             for error in report['errors']:
 191                 error['path'] = path
 192                 print('%(path)s:%(line)d:%(column)d: E%(code)s %(msg)s' % error)
 193                 ret.append(1)
 194             if warnings:
 195                 for warning in report['warnings']:
 196                     warning['path'] = path
 197                     print('%(path)s:%(line)d:%(column)d: W%(code)s %(msg)s' % warning)
 198 
 199         return 3 if ret else 0
 200 
 201     def json(self, warnings=False, output='-'):
 202         """Print out the test results in json format
 203 
 204         warnings is not respected in this output
 205         """
 206         ret = [len(r['errors']) for r in self.files.values()]
 207 
 208         with Reporter._output_handle(output) as handle:
 209             print(json.dumps(Reporter._filter_out_ok(self.files), indent=4, cls=ReporterEncoder), file=handle)
 210 
 211         return 3 if sum(ret) else 0

 214 class Validator(with_metaclass(abc.ABCMeta, object)):
 215     """Validator instances are intended to be run on a single object.  if you
 216     are scanning multiple objects for problems, you'll want to have a separate
 217     Validator for each one."""
 218 
 219     def __init__(self, reporter=None):
 220         self.reporter = reporter
 221 
 222     @abc.abstractproperty
 223     def object_name(self):
 224         """Name of the object we validated"""
 225         pass
 226 
 227     @abc.abstractproperty
 228     def object_path(self):
 229         """Path of the object we validated"""
 230         pass
 231 
 232     @abc.abstractmethod
 233     def validate(self):
 234         """Run this method to generate the test results"""
 235         pass

 238 class ModuleValidator(Validator):
 239     BLACKLIST_PATTERNS = ('.git*', '*.pyc', '*.pyo', '.*', '*.md', '*.rst', '*.txt')
 240     BLACKLIST_FILES = frozenset(('.git', '.gitignore', '.travis.yml',
 241                                  'shippable.yml',
 242                                  '.gitattributes', '.gitmodules', 'COPYING',
 243                                  '__init__.py', 'VERSION', 'test-docs.sh'))
 244     BLACKLIST = BLACKLIST_FILES.union(BLACKLIST['MODULE'])
 245 
 246     PS_DOC_BLACKLIST = frozenset((
 247         'async_status.ps1',
 248         'slurp.ps1',
 249         'setup.ps1'
 250     ))
 251     PS_ARG_VALIDATE_BLACKLIST = frozenset((
 252         'win_dsc.ps1',  # win_dsc is a dynamic arg spec, the docs won't ever match
 253     ))
 254 
 255     WHITELIST_FUTURE_IMPORTS = frozenset(('absolute_import', 'division', 'print_function'))
 256 
 257     def __init__(self, path, analyze_arg_spec=False, collection=None, collection_version=None,
 258                  base_branch=None, git_cache=None, reporter=None, routing=None):
 259         super(ModuleValidator, self).__init__(reporter=reporter or Reporter())
 260 
 261         self.path = path
 262         self.basename = os.path.basename(self.path)
 263         self.name = os.path.splitext(self.basename)[0]
 264 
 265         self.analyze_arg_spec = analyze_arg_spec
 266 
 267         self._Version = LooseVersion
 268         self._StrictVersion = StrictVersion
 269 
 270         self.collection = collection
 271         self.collection_name = 'ansible.builtin'
 272         if self.collection:
 273             self._Version = SemanticVersion
 274             self._StrictVersion = SemanticVersion
 275             collection_namespace_path, collection_name = os.path.split(self.collection)
 276             self.collection_name = '%s.%s' % (os.path.basename(collection_namespace_path), collection_name)
 277         self.routing = routing
 278         self.collection_version = None
 279         if collection_version is not None:
 280             self.collection_version_str = collection_version
 281             self.collection_version = SemanticVersion(collection_version)
 282 
 283         self.base_branch = base_branch
 284         self.git_cache = git_cache or GitCache()
 285 
 286         self._python_module_override = False
 287 
 288         with open(path) as f:
 289             self.text = f.read()
 290         self.length = len(self.text.splitlines())
 291         try:
 292             self.ast = ast.parse(self.text)
 293         except Exception:
 294             self.ast = None
 295 
 296         if base_branch:
 297             self.base_module = self._get_base_file()
 298         else:
 299             self.base_module = None
 300 
 301     def _create_version(self, v, collection_name=None):
 302         if not v:
 303             raise ValueError('Empty string is not a valid version')
 304         if collection_name == 'ansible.builtin':
 305             return LooseVersion(v)
 306         if collection_name is not None:
 307             return SemanticVersion(v)
 308         return self._Version(v)
 309 
 310     def _create_strict_version(self, v, collection_name=None):
 311         if not v:
 312             raise ValueError('Empty string is not a valid version')
 313         if collection_name == 'ansible.builtin':
 314             return StrictVersion(v)
 315         if collection_name is not None:
 316             return SemanticVersion(v)
 317         return self._StrictVersion(v)
 318 
 319     def __enter__(self):
 320         return self
 321 
 322     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_value, traceback):
 323         if not self.base_module:
 324             return
 325 
 326         try:
 327             os.remove(self.base_module)
 328         except Exception:
 329             pass
 330 
 331     @property
 332     def object_name(self):
 333         return self.basename
 334 
 335     @property
 336     def object_path(self):
 337         return self.path
 338 
 339     def _get_collection_meta(self):
 340         """Implement if we need this for version_added comparisons
 341         """
 342         pass
 343 
 344     def _python_module(self):
 345         if self.path.endswith('.py') or self._python_module_override:
 346             return True
 347         return False
 348 
 349     def _powershell_module(self):
 350         if self.path.endswith('.ps1'):
 351             return True
 352         return False
 353 
 354     def _just_docs(self):
 355         """Module can contain just docs and from __future__ boilerplate
 356         """
 357         try:
 358             for child in self.ast.body:
 359                 if not isinstance(child, ast.Assign):
 360                     # allowed from __future__ imports
 361                     if isinstance(child, ast.ImportFrom) and child.module == '__future__':
 362                         for future_import in child.names:
 363                             if future_import.name not in self.WHITELIST_FUTURE_IMPORTS:
 364                                 break
 365                         else:
 366                             continue
 367                     return False
 368             return True
 369         except AttributeError:
 370             return False
 371 
 372     def _get_base_branch_module_path(self):
 373         """List all paths within lib/ansible/modules to try and match a moved module"""
 374         return self.git_cache.base_module_paths.get(self.object_name)
 375 
 376     def _has_alias(self):
 377         """Return true if the module has any aliases."""
 378         return self.object_name in self.git_cache.head_aliased_modules
 379 
 380     def _get_base_file(self):
 381         # In case of module moves, look for the original location
 382         base_path = self._get_base_branch_module_path()
 383 
 384         command = ['git', 'show', '%s:%s' % (self.base_branch, base_path or self.path)]
 385         p = subprocess.Popen(command, stdout=subprocess.PIPE,
 386                              stderr=subprocess.PIPE)
 387         stdout, stderr = p.communicate()
 388         if int(p.returncode) != 0:
 389             return None
 390 
 391         t = tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(delete=False)
 392         t.write(stdout)
 393         t.close()
 394 
 395         return t.name
 396 
 397     def _is_new_module(self):
 398         if self._has_alias():
 399             return False
 400 
 401         return not self.object_name.startswith('_') and bool(self.base_branch) and not bool(self.base_module)
 402 
 403     def _check_interpreter(self, powershell=False):
 404         if powershell:
 405             if not self.text.startswith('#!powershell\n'):
 406                 self.reporter.error(
 407                     path=self.object_path,
 408                     code='missing-powershell-interpreter',
 409                     msg='Interpreter line is not "#!powershell"'
 410                 )
 411             return
 412 
 413         if not self.text.startswith('#!/usr/bin/python'):
 414             self.reporter.error(
 415                 path=self.object_path,
 416                 code='missing-python-interpreter',
 417                 msg='Interpreter line is not "#!/usr/bin/python"',
 418             )
 419 
 420     def _check_type_instead_of_isinstance(self, powershell=False):
 421         if powershell:
 422             return
 423         for line_no, line in enumerate(self.text.splitlines()):
 424             typekeyword = TYPE_REGEX.match(line)
 425             if typekeyword:
 426                 # TODO: add column
 427                 self.reporter.error(
 428                     path=self.object_path,
 429                     code='unidiomatic-typecheck',
 430                     msg=('Type comparison using type() found. '
 431                          'Use isinstance() instead'),
 432                     line=line_no + 1
 433                 )
 434 
 435     def _check_for_sys_exit(self):
 436         # Optimize out the happy path
 437         if 'sys.exit' not in self.text:
 438             return
 439 
 440         for line_no, line in enumerate(self.text.splitlines()):
 441             sys_exit_usage = SYS_EXIT_REGEX.match(line)
 442             if sys_exit_usage:
 443                 # TODO: add column
 444                 self.reporter.error(
 445                     path=self.object_path,
 446                     code='use-fail-json-not-sys-exit',
 447                     msg='sys.exit() call found. Should be exit_json/fail_json',
 448                     line=line_no + 1
 449                 )
 450 
 451     def _check_gpl3_header(self):
 452         header = '\n'.join(self.text.split('\n')[:20])
 453         if ('GNU General Public License' not in header or
 454                 ('version 3' not in header and 'v3.0' not in header)):
 455             self.reporter.error(
 456                 path=self.object_path,
 457                 code='missing-gplv3-license',
 458                 msg='GPLv3 license header not found in the first 20 lines of the module'
 459             )
 460         elif self._is_new_module():
 461             if len([line for line in header
 462                     if 'GNU General Public License' in line]) > 1:
 463                 self.reporter.error(
 464                     path=self.object_path,
 465                     code='use-short-gplv3-license',
 466                     msg='Found old style GPLv3 license header: '
 467                         'https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/devel/dev_guide/developing_modules_documenting.html#copyright'
 468                 )
 469 
 470     def _check_for_subprocess(self):
 471         for child in self.ast.body:
 472             if isinstance(child, ast.Import):
 473                 if child.names[0].name == 'subprocess':
 474                     for line_no, line in enumerate(self.text.splitlines()):
 475                         sp_match = SUBPROCESS_REGEX.search(line)
 476                         if sp_match:
 477                             self.reporter.error(
 478                                 path=self.object_path,
 479                                 code='use-run-command-not-popen',
 480                                 msg=('subprocess.Popen call found. Should be module.run_command'),
 481                                 line=(line_no + 1),
 482                                 column=(sp_match.span()[0] + 1)
 483                             )
 484 
 485     def _check_for_os_call(self):
 486         if 'os.call' in self.text:
 487             for line_no, line in enumerate(self.text.splitlines()):
 488                 os_call_match = OS_CALL_REGEX.search(line)
 489                 if os_call_match:
 490                     self.reporter.error(
 491                         path=self.object_path,
 492                         code='use-run-command-not-os-call',
 493                         msg=('os.call() call found. Should be module.run_command'),
 494                         line=(line_no + 1),
 495                         column=(os_call_match.span()[0] + 1)
 496                     )
 497 
 498     def _find_blacklist_imports(self):
 499         for child in self.ast.body:
 500             names = []
 501             if isinstance(child, ast.Import):
 502                 names.extend(child.names)
 503             elif isinstance(child, TRY_EXCEPT):
 504                 bodies = child.body
 505                 for handler in child.handlers:
 506                     bodies.extend(handler.body)
 507                 for grandchild in bodies:
 508                     if isinstance(grandchild, ast.Import):
 509                         names.extend(grandchild.names)
 510             for name in names:
 511                 # TODO: Add line/col
 512                 for blacklist_import, options in BLACKLIST_IMPORTS.items():
 513                     if re.search(blacklist_import, name.name):
 514                         new_only = options['new_only']
 515                         if self._is_new_module() and new_only:
 516                             self.reporter.error(
 517                                 path=self.object_path,
 518                                 **options['error']
 519                             )
 520                         elif not new_only:
 521                             self.reporter.error(
 522                                 path=self.object_path,
 523                                 **options['error']
 524                             )
 525 
 526     def _find_module_utils(self, main):
 527         linenos = []
 528         found_basic = False
 529         for child in self.ast.body:
 530             if isinstance(child, (ast.Import, ast.ImportFrom)):
 531                 names = []
 532                 try:
 533                     names.append(child.module)
 534                     if child.module.endswith('.basic'):
 535                         found_basic = True
 536                 except AttributeError:
 537                     pass
 538                 names.extend([n.name for n in child.names])
 539 
 540                 if [n for n in names if n.startswith('ansible.module_utils')]:
 541                     linenos.append(child.lineno)
 542 
 543                     for name in child.names:
 544                         if ('module_utils' in getattr(child, 'module', '') and
 545                                 isinstance(name, ast.alias) and
 546                                 name.name == '*'):
 547                             msg = (
 548                                 'module-utils-specific-import',
 549                                 ('module_utils imports should import specific '
 550                                  'components, not "*"')
 551                             )
 552                             if self._is_new_module():
 553                                 self.reporter.error(
 554                                     path=self.object_path,
 555                                     code=msg[0],
 556                                     msg=msg[1],
 557                                     line=child.lineno
 558                                 )
 559                             else:
 560                                 self.reporter.warning(
 561                                     path=self.object_path,
 562                                     code=msg[0],
 563                                     msg=msg[1],
 564                                     line=child.lineno
 565                                 )
 566 
 567                         if (isinstance(name, ast.alias) and
 568                                 name.name == 'basic'):
 569                             found_basic = True
 570 
 571         if not found_basic:
 572             self.reporter.warning(
 573                 path=self.object_path,
 574                 code='missing-module-utils-basic-import',
 575                 msg='Did not find "ansible.module_utils.basic" import'
 576             )
 577 
 578         return linenos
 579 
 580     def _get_first_callable(self):
 581         linenos = []
 582         for child in self.ast.body:
 583             if isinstance(child, (ast.FunctionDef, ast.ClassDef)):
 584                 linenos.append(child.lineno)
 585 
 586         return min(linenos)
 587 
 588     def _find_main_call(self, look_for="main"):
 589         """ Ensure that the module ends with:
 590             if __name__ == '__main__':
 591                 main()
 592         OR, in the case of modules that are in the docs-only deprecation phase
 593             if __name__ == '__main__':
 594                 removed_module()
 595         """
 596         lineno = False
 597         if_bodies = []
 598         for child in self.ast.body:
 599             if isinstance(child, ast.If):
 600                 try:
 601                     if child.test.left.id == '__name__':
 602                         if_bodies.extend(child.body)
 603                 except AttributeError:
 604                     pass
 605 
 606         bodies = self.ast.body
 607         bodies.extend(if_bodies)
 608 
 609         for child in bodies:
 610 
 611             # validate that the next to last line is 'if __name__ == "__main__"'
 612             if child.lineno == (self.length - 1):
 613 
 614                 mainchecked = False
 615                 try:
 616                     if isinstance(child, ast.If) and \
 617                             child.test.left.id == '__name__' and \
 618                             len(child.test.ops) == 1 and \
 619                             isinstance(child.test.ops[0], ast.Eq) and \
 620                             child.test.comparators[0].s == '__main__':
 621                         mainchecked = True
 622                 except Exception:
 623                     pass
 624 
 625                 if not mainchecked:
 626                     self.reporter.error(
 627                         path=self.object_path,
 628                         code='missing-if-name-main',
 629                         msg='Next to last line should be: if __name__ == "__main__":',
 630                         line=child.lineno
 631                     )
 632 
 633             # validate that the final line is a call to main()
 634             if isinstance(child, ast.Expr):
 635                 if isinstance(child.value, ast.Call):
 636                     if (isinstance(child.value.func, ast.Name) and
 637                             child.value.func.id == look_for):
 638                         lineno = child.lineno
 639                         if lineno < self.length - 1:
 640                             self.reporter.error(
 641                                 path=self.object_path,
 642                                 code='last-line-main-call',
 643                                 msg=('Call to %s() not the last line' % look_for),
 644                                 line=lineno
 645                             )
 646 
 647         if not lineno:
 648             self.reporter.error(
 649                 path=self.object_path,
 650                 code='missing-main-call',
 651                 msg=('Did not find a call to %s()' % look_for)
 652             )
 653 
 654         return lineno or 0

 656     def _find_has_import(self):
 657         for child in self.ast.body:
 658             found_try_except_import = False
 659             found_has = False
 660             if isinstance(child, TRY_EXCEPT):
 661                 bodies = child.body
 662                 for handler in child.handlers:
 663                     bodies.extend(handler.body)
 664                 for grandchild in bodies:
 665                     if isinstance(grandchild, ast.Import):
 666                         found_try_except_import = True
 667                     if isinstance(grandchild, ast.Assign):
 668                         for target in grandchild.targets:
 669                             if target.id.lower().startswith('has_'):
 670                                 found_has = True
 671             if found_try_except_import and not found_has:
 672                 # TODO: Add line/col
 673                 self.reporter.warning(
 674                     path=self.object_path,
 675                     code='try-except-missing-has',
 676                     msg='Found Try/Except block without HAS_ assignment'
 677                 )

 679     def _ensure_imports_below_docs(self, doc_info, first_callable):
 680         try:
 681             min_doc_line = min(
 682                 [doc_info[key]['lineno'] for key in doc_info if doc_info[key]['lineno']]
 683             )
 684         except ValueError:
 685             # We can't perform this validation, as there are no DOCs provided at all
 686             return
 687 
 688         max_doc_line = max(
 689             [doc_info[key]['end_lineno'] for key in doc_info if doc_info[key]['end_lineno']]
 690         )
 691 
 692         import_lines = []
 693 
 694         for child in self.ast.body:
 695             if isinstance(child, (ast.Import, ast.ImportFrom)):
 696                 if isinstance(child, ast.ImportFrom) and child.module == '__future__':
 697                     # allowed from __future__ imports
 698                     for future_import in child.names:
 699                         if future_import.name not in self.WHITELIST_FUTURE_IMPORTS:
 700                             self.reporter.error(
 701                                 path=self.object_path,
 702                                 code='illegal-future-imports',
 703                                 msg=('Only the following from __future__ imports are allowed: %s'
 704                                      % ', '.join(self.WHITELIST_FUTURE_IMPORTS)),
 705                                 line=child.lineno
 706                             )
 707                             break
 708                     else:  # for-else.  If we didn't find a problem nad break out of the loop, then this is a legal import
 709                         continue
 710                 import_lines.append(child.lineno)
 711                 if child.lineno < min_doc_line:
 712                     self.reporter.error(
 713                         path=self.object_path,
 714                         code='import-before-documentation',
 715                         msg=('Import found before documentation variables. '
 716                              'All imports must appear below '
 717                              'DOCUMENTATION/EXAMPLES/RETURN.'),
 718                         line=child.lineno
 719                     )
 720                     break
 721             elif isinstance(child, TRY_EXCEPT):
 722                 bodies = child.body
 723                 for handler in child.handlers:
 724                     bodies.extend(handler.body)
 725                 for grandchild in bodies:
 726                     if isinstance(grandchild, (ast.Import, ast.ImportFrom)):
 727                         import_lines.append(grandchild.lineno)
 728                         if grandchild.lineno < min_doc_line:
 729                             self.reporter.error(
 730                                 path=self.object_path,
 731                                 code='import-before-documentation',
 732                                 msg=('Import found before documentation '
 733                                      'variables. All imports must appear below '
 734                                      'DOCUMENTATION/EXAMPLES/RETURN.'),
 735                                 line=child.lineno
 736                             )
 737                             break
 738 
 739         for import_line in import_lines:
 740             if not (max_doc_line < import_line < first_callable):
 741                 msg = (
 742                     'import-placement',
 743                     ('Imports should be directly below DOCUMENTATION/EXAMPLES/'
 744                      'RETURN.')
 745                 )
 746                 if self._is_new_module():
 747                     self.reporter.error(
 748                         path=self.object_path,
 749                         code=msg[0],
 750                         msg=msg[1],
 751                         line=import_line
 752                     )
 753                 else:
 754                     self.reporter.warning(
 755                         path=self.object_path,
 756                         code=msg[0],
 757                         msg=msg[1],
 758                         line=import_line
 759                     )
 760 
 761     def _validate_ps_replacers(self):
 762         # loop all (for/else + error)
 763         # get module list for each
 764         # check "shape" of each module name
 765 
 766         module_requires = r'(?im)^#\s*requires\s+\-module(?:s?)\s*(Ansible\.ModuleUtils\..+)'
 767         csharp_requires = r'(?im)^#\s*ansiblerequires\s+\-csharputil\s*(Ansible\..+)'
 768         found_requires = False
 769 
 770         for req_stmt in re.finditer(module_requires, self.text):
 771             found_requires = True
 772             # this will bomb on dictionary format - "don't do that"
 773             module_list = [x.strip() for x in req_stmt.group(1).split(',')]
 774             if len(module_list) > 1:
 775                 self.reporter.error(
 776                     path=self.object_path,
 777                     code='multiple-utils-per-requires',
 778                     msg='Ansible.ModuleUtils requirements do not support multiple modules per statement: "%s"' % req_stmt.group(0)
 779                 )
 780                 continue
 781 
 782             module_name = module_list[0]
 783 
 784             if module_name.lower().endswith('.psm1'):
 785                 self.reporter.error(
 786                     path=self.object_path,
 787                     code='invalid-requires-extension',
 788                     msg='Module #Requires should not end in .psm1: "%s"' % module_name
 789                 )
 790 
 791         for req_stmt in re.finditer(csharp_requires, self.text):
 792             found_requires = True
 793             # this will bomb on dictionary format - "don't do that"
 794             module_list = [x.strip() for x in req_stmt.group(1).split(',')]
 795             if len(module_list) > 1:
 796                 self.reporter.error(
 797                     path=self.object_path,
 798                     code='multiple-csharp-utils-per-requires',
 799                     msg='Ansible C# util requirements do not support multiple utils per statement: "%s"' % req_stmt.group(0)
 800                 )
 801                 continue
 802 
 803             module_name = module_list[0]
 804 
 805             if module_name.lower().endswith('.cs'):
 806                 self.reporter.error(
 807                     path=self.object_path,
 808                     code='illegal-extension-cs',
 809                     msg='Module #AnsibleRequires -CSharpUtil should not end in .cs: "%s"' % module_name
 810                 )
 811 
 812         # also accept the legacy #POWERSHELL_COMMON replacer signal
 813         if not found_requires and REPLACER_WINDOWS not in self.text:
 814             self.reporter.error(
 815                 path=self.object_path,
 816                 code='missing-module-utils-import-csharp-requirements',
 817                 msg='No Ansible.ModuleUtils or C# Ansible util requirements/imports found'
 818             )

 820     def _find_ps_docs_py_file(self):
 821         if self.object_name in self.PS_DOC_BLACKLIST:
 822             return
 823         py_path = self.path.replace('.ps1', '.py')

 832     def _get_docs(self):
 833         docs = {
 834             'DOCUMENTATION': {
 835                 'value': None,
 836                 'lineno': 0,
 837                 'end_lineno': 0,
 838             },
 839             'EXAMPLES': {
 840                 'value': None,
 841                 'lineno': 0,
 842                 'end_lineno': 0,
 843             },
 844             'RETURN': {
 845                 'value': None,
 846                 'lineno': 0,
 847                 'end_lineno': 0,
 848             },
 849         }
 850         for child in self.ast.body:
 851             if isinstance(child, ast.Assign):
 852                 for grandchild in child.targets:
 853                     if not isinstance(grandchild, ast.Name):
 854                         continue
 855 
 856                     if grandchild.id == 'DOCUMENTATION':
 857                         docs['DOCUMENTATION']['value'] = child.value.s
 858                         docs['DOCUMENTATION']['lineno'] = child.lineno
 859                         docs['DOCUMENTATION']['end_lineno'] = (
 860                             child.lineno + len(child.value.s.splitlines())
 861                         )
 862                     elif grandchild.id == 'EXAMPLES':
 863                         docs['EXAMPLES']['value'] = child.value.s
 864                         docs['EXAMPLES']['lineno'] = child.lineno
 865                         docs['EXAMPLES']['end_lineno'] = (
 866                             child.lineno + len(child.value.s.splitlines())
 867                         )
 868                     elif grandchild.id == 'RETURN':
 869                         docs['RETURN']['value'] = child.value.s
 870                         docs['RETURN']['lineno'] = child.lineno
 871                         docs['RETURN']['end_lineno'] = (
 872                             child.lineno + len(child.value.s.splitlines())
 873                         )
 874 
 875         return docs

 877     def _validate_docs_schema(self, doc, schema, name, error_code):
 878         # TODO: Add line/col
 879         errors = []
 880         try:
 881             schema(doc)
 882         except Exception as e:
 883             for error in e.errors:
 884                 error.data = doc
 885             errors.extend(e.errors)
 886 
 887         for error in errors:
 888             path = [str(p) for p in error.path]
 889 
 890             local_error_code = getattr(error, 'ansible_error_code', error_code)
 891 
 892             if isinstance(error.data, dict):
 893                 error_message = humanize_error(error.data, error)
 894             else:
 895                 error_message = error
 896 
 897             if path:
 898                 combined_path = '%s.%s' % (name, '.'.join(path))
 899             else:
 900                 combined_path = name
 901 
 902             self.reporter.error(
 903                 path=self.object_path,
 904                 code=local_error_code,
 905                 msg='%s: %s' % (combined_path, error_message)
 906             )

 908     def _validate_docs(self):
 909         doc_info = self._get_docs()
 910         doc = None
 911         documentation_exists = False
 912         examples_exist = False
 913         returns_exist = False
 914         # We have three ways of marking deprecated/removed files.  Have to check each one
 915         # individually and then make sure they all agree
 916         filename_deprecated_or_removed = False
 917         deprecated = False
 918         removed = False
 919         doc_deprecated = None  # doc legally might not exist
 920         routing_says_deprecated = False
 921 
 922         if self.object_name.startswith('_') and not os.path.islink(self.object_path):
 923             filename_deprecated_or_removed = True
 924 
 925         # We are testing a collection
 926         if self.routing:
 927             routing_deprecation = self.routing.get('plugin_routing', {}).get('modules', {}).get(self.name, {}).get('deprecation', {})
 928             if routing_deprecation:
 929                 # meta/runtime.yml says this is deprecated
 930                 routing_says_deprecated = True
 931                 deprecated = True
 932 
 933         if not removed:
 934             if not bool(doc_info['DOCUMENTATION']['value']):
 935                 self.reporter.error(
 936                     path=self.object_path,
 937                     code='missing-documentation',
 938                     msg='No DOCUMENTATION provided'
 939                 )
 940             else:
 941                 documentation_exists = True
 942                 doc, errors, traces = parse_yaml(
 943                     doc_info['DOCUMENTATION']['value'],
 944                     doc_info['DOCUMENTATION']['lineno'],
 945                     self.name, 'DOCUMENTATION'
 946                 )
 947                 if doc:
 948                     add_collection_to_versions_and_dates(doc, self.collection_name, is_module=True)
 949                 for error in errors:
 950                     self.reporter.error(
 951                         path=self.object_path,
 952                         code='documentation-syntax-error',
 953                         **error
 954                     )
 955                 for trace in traces:
 956                     self.reporter.trace(
 957                         path=self.object_path,
 958                         tracebk=trace
 959                     )
 960                 if not errors and not traces:
 961                     missing_fragment = False
 962                     with CaptureStd():
 963                         try:
 964                             get_docstring(self.path, fragment_loader, verbose=True,
 965                                           collection_name=self.collection_name, is_module=True)
 966                         except AssertionError:
 967                             fragment = doc['extends_documentation_fragment']
 968                             self.reporter.error(
 969                                 path=self.object_path,
 970                                 code='missing-doc-fragment',
 971                                 msg='DOCUMENTATION fragment missing: %s' % fragment
 972                             )
 973                             missing_fragment = True
 974                         except Exception as e:
 975                             self.reporter.trace(
 976                                 path=self.object_path,
 977                                 tracebk=traceback.format_exc()
 978                             )
 979                             self.reporter.error(
 980                                 path=self.object_path,
 981                                 code='documentation-error',
 982                                 msg='Unknown DOCUMENTATION error, see TRACE: %s' % e
 983                             )
 984 
 985                     if not missing_fragment:
 986                         add_fragments(doc, self.object_path, fragment_loader=fragment_loader, is_module=True)
 987 
 988                     if 'options' in doc and doc['options'] is None:
 989                         self.reporter.error(
 990                             path=self.object_path,
 991                             code='invalid-documentation-options',
 992                             msg='DOCUMENTATION.options must be a dictionary/hash when used',
 993                         )
 994 
 995                     if 'deprecated' in doc and doc.get('deprecated'):
 996                         doc_deprecated = True
 997                         doc_deprecation = doc['deprecated']
 998                         documentation_collection = doc_deprecation.get('removed_from_collection')
 999                         if documentation_collection != self.collection_name:
1000                             self.reporter.error(
1001                                 path=self.object_path,
1002                                 code='deprecation-wrong-collection',
1003                                 msg='"DOCUMENTATION.deprecation.removed_from_collection must be the current collection name: %r vs. %r' % (
1004                                     documentation_collection, self.collection_name)
1005                             )
1006                     else:
1007                         doc_deprecated = False
1008 
1009                     if os.path.islink(self.object_path):
1010                         # This module has an alias, which we can tell as it's a symlink
1011                         # Rather than checking for `module: $filename` we need to check against the true filename
1012                         self._validate_docs_schema(
1013                             doc,
1014                             doc_schema(
1015                                 os.readlink(self.object_path).split('.')[0],
1016                                 for_collection=bool(self.collection),
1017                                 deprecated_module=deprecated,
1018                             ),
1019                             'DOCUMENTATION',
1020                             'invalid-documentation',
1021                         )
1022                     else:
1023                         # This is the normal case
1024                         self._validate_docs_schema(
1025                             doc,
1026                             doc_schema(
1027                                 self.object_name.split('.')[0],
1028                                 for_collection=bool(self.collection),
1029                                 deprecated_module=deprecated,
1030                             ),
1031                             'DOCUMENTATION',
1032                             'invalid-documentation',
1033                         )
1034 
1035                     if not self.collection:
1036                         existing_doc = self._check_for_new_args(doc)
1037                         self._check_version_added(doc, existing_doc)
1038 
1039             if not bool(doc_info['EXAMPLES']['value']):
1040                 self.reporter.error(
1041                     path=self.object_path,
1042                     code='missing-examples',
1043                     msg='No EXAMPLES provided'
1044                 )
1045             else:
1046                 _doc, errors, traces = parse_yaml(doc_info['EXAMPLES']['value'],
1047                                                   doc_info['EXAMPLES']['lineno'],
1048                                                   self.name, 'EXAMPLES', load_all=True)
1049                 for error in errors:
1050                     self.reporter.error(
1051                         path=self.object_path,
1052                         code='invalid-examples',
1053                         **error
1054                     )
1055                 for trace in traces:
1056                     self.reporter.trace(
1057                         path=self.object_path,
1058                         tracebk=trace
1059                     )
1060 
1061             if not bool(doc_info['RETURN']['value']):
1062                 if self._is_new_module():
1063                     self.reporter.error(
1064                         path=self.object_path,
1065                         code='missing-return',
1066                         msg='No RETURN provided'
1067                     )
1068                 else:
1069                     self.reporter.warning(
1070                         path=self.object_path,
1071                         code='missing-return-legacy',
1072                         msg='No RETURN provided'
1073                     )
1074             else:
1075                 data, errors, traces = parse_yaml(doc_info['RETURN']['value'],
1076                                                   doc_info['RETURN']['lineno'],
1077                                                   self.name, 'RETURN')
1078                 if data:
1079                     add_collection_to_versions_and_dates(data, self.collection_name, is_module=True, return_docs=True)
1080                 self._validate_docs_schema(data, return_schema(for_collection=bool(self.collection)),
1081                                            'RETURN', 'return-syntax-error')
1082 
1083                 for error in errors:
1084                     self.reporter.error(
1085                         path=self.object_path,
1086                         code='return-syntax-error',
1087                         **error
1088                     )
1089                 for trace in traces:
1090                     self.reporter.trace(
1091                         path=self.object_path,
1092                         tracebk=trace
1093                     )
1094 
1095         # Check for mismatched deprecation
1096         if not self.collection:
1097             mismatched_deprecation = True
1098             if not (filename_deprecated_or_removed or removed or deprecated or doc_deprecated):
1099                 mismatched_deprecation = False
1100             else:
1101                 if (filename_deprecated_or_removed and deprecated and doc_deprecated):
1102                     mismatched_deprecation = False
1103                 if (filename_deprecated_or_removed and removed and not (documentation_exists or examples_exist or returns_exist)):
1104                     mismatched_deprecation = False
1105 
1106             if mismatched_deprecation:
1107                 self.reporter.error(
1108                     path=self.object_path,
1109                     code='deprecation-mismatch',
1110                     msg='Module deprecation/removed must agree in documentaiton, by prepending filename with'
1111                         ' "_", and setting DOCUMENTATION.deprecated for deprecation or by removing all'
1112                         ' documentation for removed'
1113                 )
1114         else:
1115             # We are testing a collection
1116             if self.object_name.startswith('_'):
1117                 self.reporter.error(
1118                     path=self.object_path,
1119                     code='collections-no-underscore-on-deprecation',
1120                     msg='Deprecated content in collections MUST NOT start with "_", update meta/runtime.yml instead',
1121                 )
1122 
1123             if not (doc_deprecated == routing_says_deprecated):
1124                 # DOCUMENTATION.deprecated and meta/runtime.yml disagree
1125                 self.reporter.error(
1126                     path=self.object_path,
1127                     code='deprecation-mismatch',
1128                     msg='"meta/runtime.yml" and DOCUMENTATION.deprecation do not agree.'
1129                 )
1130             elif routing_says_deprecated:
1131                 # Both DOCUMENTATION.deprecated and meta/runtime.yml agree that the module is deprecated.
1132                 # Make sure they give the same version or date.
1133                 routing_date = routing_deprecation.get('removal_date')
1134                 routing_version = routing_deprecation.get('removal_version')
1135                 # The versions and dates in the module documentation are auto-tagged, so remove the tag
1136                 # to make comparison possible and to avoid confusing the user.
1137                 documentation_date = doc_deprecation.get('removed_at_date')
1138                 documentation_version = doc_deprecation.get('removed_in')
1139                 if not compare_dates(routing_date, documentation_date):
1140                     self.reporter.error(
1141                         path=self.object_path,
1142                         code='deprecation-mismatch',
1143                         msg='"meta/runtime.yml" and DOCUMENTATION.deprecation do not agree on removal date: %r vs. %r' % (
1144                             routing_date, documentation_date)
1145                     )
1146                 if routing_version != documentation_version:
1147                     self.reporter.error(
1148                         path=self.object_path,
1149                         code='deprecation-mismatch',
1150                         msg='"meta/runtime.yml" and DOCUMENTATION.deprecation do not agree on removal version: %r vs. %r' % (
1151                             routing_version, documentation_version)
1152                     )
1153 
1154             # In the future we should error if ANSIBLE_METADATA exists in a collection
1155 
1156         return doc_info, doc

1158     def _check_version_added(self, doc, existing_doc):
1159         version_added_raw = doc.get('version_added')
1160         try:
1161             collection_name = doc.get('version_added_collection')
1162             version_added = self._create_strict_version(
1163                 str(doc.get('version_added', '0.0') or '0.0'),
1164                 collection_name=collection_name)
1165         except ValueError as e:
1166             version_added = doc.get('version_added', '0.0')
1167             if version_added != 'historical' or self._is_new_module():
1168                 self.reporter.error(
1169                     path=self.object_path,
1170                     code='module-invalid-version-added',
1171                     msg='version_added is not a valid version number: %r. Error: %s' % (version_added, e)
1172                 )
1173                 return
1174 
1175         if existing_doc and str(version_added_raw) != str(existing_doc.get('version_added')):
1176             self.reporter.error(
1177                 path=self.object_path,
1178                 code='module-incorrect-version-added',
1179                 msg='version_added should be %r. Currently %r' % (existing_doc.get('version_added'), version_added_raw)
1180             )
1181 
1182         if not self._is_new_module():
1183             return
1184 
1185         should_be = '.'.join(ansible_version.split('.')[:2])
1186         strict_ansible_version = self._create_strict_version(should_be, collection_name='ansible.builtin')
1187 
1188         if (version_added < strict_ansible_version or
1189                 strict_ansible_version < version_added):
1190             self.reporter.error(
1191                 path=self.object_path,
1192                 code='module-incorrect-version-added',
1193                 msg='version_added should be %r. Currently %r' % (should_be, version_added_raw)
1194             )

1196     def _validate_ansible_module_call(self, docs):
1197         try:
1198             spec, args, kwargs = get_argument_spec(self.path, self.collection)
1199         except AnsibleModuleNotInitialized:
1200             self.reporter.error(
1201                 path=self.object_path,
1202                 code='ansible-module-not-initialized',
1203                 msg="Execution of the module did not result in initialization of AnsibleModule",
1204             )
1205             return
1206         except AnsibleModuleImportError as e:
1207             self.reporter.error(
1208                 path=self.object_path,
1209                 code='import-error',
1210                 msg="Exception attempting to import module for argument_spec introspection, '%s'" % e
1211             )
1212             self.reporter.trace(
1213                 path=self.object_path,
1214                 tracebk=traceback.format_exc()
1215             )
1216             return
1217 
1218         self._validate_docs_schema(kwargs, ansible_module_kwargs_schema(for_collection=bool(self.collection)),
1219                                    'AnsibleModule', 'invalid-ansiblemodule-schema')
1220 
1221         self._validate_argument_spec(docs, spec, kwargs)

1223     def _validate_list_of_module_args(self, name, terms, spec, context):
1224         if terms is None:
1225             return
1226         if not isinstance(terms, (list, tuple)):
1227             # This is already reported by schema checking
1228             return
1229         for check in terms:
1230             if not isinstance(check, (list, tuple)):
1231                 # This is already reported by schema checking
1232                 continue
1233             bad_term = False
1234             for term in check:
1235                 if not isinstance(term, string_types):
1236                     msg = name
1237                     if context:
1238                         msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1239                     msg += " must contain strings in the lists or tuples; found value %r" % (term, )
1240                     self.reporter.error(
1241                         path=self.object_path,
1242                         code=name + '-type',
1243                         msg=msg,
1244                     )
1245                     bad_term = True
1246             if bad_term:
1247                 continue
1248             if len(set(check)) != len(check):
1249                 msg = name
1250                 if context:
1251                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1252                 msg += " has repeated terms"
1253                 self.reporter.error(
1254                     path=self.object_path,
1255                     code=name + '-collision',
1256                     msg=msg,
1257                 )
1258             if not set(check) <= set(spec):
1259                 msg = name
1260                 if context:
1261                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1262                 msg += " contains terms which are not part of argument_spec: %s" % ", ".join(sorted(set(check).difference(set(spec))))
1263                 self.reporter.error(
1264                     path=self.object_path,
1265                     code=name + '-unknown',
1266                     msg=msg,
1267                 )

1269     def _validate_required_if(self, terms, spec, context, module):
1270         if terms is None:
1271             return
1272         if not isinstance(terms, (list, tuple)):
1273             # This is already reported by schema checking
1274             return
1275         for check in terms:
1276             if not isinstance(check, (list, tuple)) or len(check) not in [3, 4]:
1277                 # This is already reported by schema checking
1278                 continue
1279             if len(check) == 4 and not isinstance(check[3], bool):
1280                 msg = "required_if"
1281                 if context:
1282                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1283                 msg += " must have forth value omitted or of type bool; got %r" % (check[3], )
1284                 self.reporter.error(
1285                     path=self.object_path,
1286                     code='required_if-is_one_of-type',
1287                     msg=msg,
1288                 )
1289             requirements = check[2]
1290             if not isinstance(requirements, (list, tuple)):
1291                 msg = "required_if"
1292                 if context:
1293                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1294                 msg += " must have third value (requirements) being a list or tuple; got type %r" % (requirements, )
1295                 self.reporter.error(
1296                     path=self.object_path,
1297                     code='required_if-requirements-type',
1298                     msg=msg,
1299                 )
1300                 continue
1301             bad_term = False
1302             for term in requirements:
1303                 if not isinstance(term, string_types):
1304                     msg = "required_if"
1305                     if context:
1306                         msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1307                     msg += " must have only strings in third value (requirements); got %r" % (term, )
1308                     self.reporter.error(
1309                         path=self.object_path,
1310                         code='required_if-requirements-type',
1311                         msg=msg,
1312                     )
1313                     bad_term = True
1314             if bad_term:
1315                 continue
1316             if len(set(requirements)) != len(requirements):
1317                 msg = "required_if"
1318                 if context:
1319                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1320                 msg += " has repeated terms in requirements"
1321                 self.reporter.error(
1322                     path=self.object_path,
1323                     code='required_if-requirements-collision',
1324                     msg=msg,
1325                 )
1326             if not set(requirements) <= set(spec):
1327                 msg = "required_if"
1328                 if context:
1329                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1330                 msg += " contains terms in requirements which are not part of argument_spec: %s" % ", ".join(sorted(set(requirements).difference(set(spec))))
1331                 self.reporter.error(
1332                     path=self.object_path,
1333                     code='required_if-requirements-unknown',
1334                     msg=msg,
1335                 )
1336             key = check[0]
1337             if key not in spec:
1338                 msg = "required_if"
1339                 if context:
1340                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1341                 msg += " must have its key %s in argument_spec" % key
1342                 self.reporter.error(
1343                     path=self.object_path,
1344                     code='required_if-unknown-key',
1345                     msg=msg,
1346                 )
1347                 continue
1348             if key in requirements:
1349                 msg = "required_if"
1350                 if context:
1351                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1352                 msg += " contains its key %s in requirements" % key
1353                 self.reporter.error(
1354                     path=self.object_path,
1355                     code='required_if-key-in-requirements',
1356                     msg=msg,
1357                 )
1358             value = check[1]
1359             if value is not None:
1360                 _type = spec[key].get('type', 'str')
1361                 if callable(_type):
1362                     _type_checker = _type
1363                 else:
1364                     _type_checker = module._CHECK_ARGUMENT_TYPES_DISPATCHER.get(_type)
1365                 try:
1366                     with CaptureStd():
1367                         dummy = _type_checker(value)
1368                 except (Exception, SystemExit):
1369                     msg = "required_if"
1370                     if context:
1371                         msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1372                     msg += " has value %r which does not fit to %s's parameter type %r" % (value, key, _type)
1373                     self.reporter.error(
1374                         path=self.object_path,
1375                         code='required_if-value-type',
1376                         msg=msg,
1377                     )

1379     def _validate_required_by(self, terms, spec, context):
1380         if terms is None:
1381             return
1382         if not isinstance(terms, Mapping):
1383             # This is already reported by schema checking
1384             return
1385         for key, value in terms.items():
1386             if isinstance(value, string_types):
1387                 value = [value]
1388             if not isinstance(value, (list, tuple)):
1389                 # This is already reported by schema checking
1390                 continue
1391             for term in value:
1392                 if not isinstance(term, string_types):
1393                     # This is already reported by schema checking
1394                     continue
1395             if len(set(value)) != len(value) or key in value:
1396                 msg = "required_by"
1397                 if context:
1398                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1399                 msg += " has repeated terms"
1400                 self.reporter.error(
1401                     path=self.object_path,
1402                     code='required_by-collision',
1403                     msg=msg,
1404                 )
1405             if not set(value) <= set(spec) or key not in spec:
1406                 msg = "required_by"
1407                 if context:
1408                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1409                 msg += " contains terms which are not part of argument_spec: %s" % ", ".join(sorted(set(value).difference(set(spec))))
1410                 self.reporter.error(
1411                     path=self.object_path,
1412                     code='required_by-unknown',
1413                     msg=msg,
1414                 )
