1416     def _validate_argument_spec(self, docs, spec, kwargs, context=None, last_context_spec=None):
1417         if not self.analyze_arg_spec:
1418             return
1419 
1420         if docs is None:
1421             docs = {}
1422 
1423         if context is None:
1424             context = []
1425 
1426         if last_context_spec is None:
1427             last_context_spec = kwargs
1428 
1429         try:
1430             if not context:
1431                 add_fragments(docs, self.object_path, fragment_loader=fragment_loader, is_module=True)
1432         except Exception:
1433             # Cannot merge fragments
1434             return
1435 
1436         # Use this to access type checkers later
1437         module = NoArgsAnsibleModule({})
1438 
1439         self._validate_list_of_module_args('mutually_exclusive', last_context_spec.get('mutually_exclusive'), spec, context)
1440         self._validate_list_of_module_args('required_together', last_context_spec.get('required_together'), spec, context)
1441         self._validate_list_of_module_args('required_one_of', last_context_spec.get('required_one_of'), spec, context)
1442         self._validate_required_if(last_context_spec.get('required_if'), spec, context, module)
1443         self._validate_required_by(last_context_spec.get('required_by'), spec, context)
1444 
1445         provider_args = set()
1446         args_from_argspec = set()
1447         deprecated_args_from_argspec = set()
1448         doc_options = docs.get('options', {})
1449         if doc_options is None:
1450             doc_options = {}
1451         for arg, data in spec.items():
1452             restricted_argument_names = ('message', 'syslog_facility')
1453             if arg.lower() in restricted_argument_names:
1454                 msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec " % arg
1455                 if context:
1456                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1457                 msg += "must not be one of %s as it is used " \
1458                        "internally by Ansible Core Engine" % (",".join(restricted_argument_names))
1459                 self.reporter.error(
1460                     path=self.object_path,
1461                     code='invalid-argument-name',
1462                     msg=msg,
1463                 )
1464                 continue
1465             if 'aliases' in data:
1466                 for al in data['aliases']:
1467                     if al.lower() in restricted_argument_names:
1468                         msg = "Argument alias '%s' in argument_spec " % al
1469                         if context:
1470                             msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1471                         msg += "must not be one of %s as it is used " \
1472                                "internally by Ansible Core Engine" % (",".join(restricted_argument_names))
1473                         self.reporter.error(
1474                             path=self.object_path,
1475                             code='invalid-argument-name',
1476                             msg=msg,
1477                         )
1478                         continue
1479 
1480             if not isinstance(data, dict):
1481                 msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1482                 if context:
1483                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1484                 msg += " must be a dictionary/hash when used"
1485                 self.reporter.error(
1486                     path=self.object_path,
1487                     code='invalid-argument-spec',
1488                     msg=msg,
1489                 )
1490                 continue
1491 
1492             removed_at_date = data.get('removed_at_date', None)
1493             if removed_at_date is not None:
1494                 try:
1495                     if parse_isodate(removed_at_date, allow_date=False) < datetime.date.today():
1496                         msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1497                         if context:
1498                             msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1499                         msg += " has a removed_at_date '%s' before today" % removed_at_date
1500                         self.reporter.error(
1501                             path=self.object_path,
1502                             code='deprecated-date',
1503                             msg=msg,
1504                         )
1505                 except ValueError:
1506                     # This should only happen when removed_at_date is not in ISO format. Since schema
1507                     # validation already reported this as an error, don't report it a second time.
1508                     pass
1509 
1510             deprecated_aliases = data.get('deprecated_aliases', None)
1511             if deprecated_aliases is not None:
1512                 for deprecated_alias in deprecated_aliases:
1513                     if 'name' in deprecated_alias and 'date' in deprecated_alias:
1514                         try:
1515                             date = deprecated_alias['date']
1516                             if parse_isodate(date, allow_date=False) < datetime.date.today():
1517                                 msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1518                                 if context:
1519                                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1520                                 msg += " has deprecated aliases '%s' with removal date '%s' before today" % (
1521                                     deprecated_alias['name'], deprecated_alias['date'])
1522                                 self.reporter.error(
1523                                     path=self.object_path,
1524                                     code='deprecated-date',
1525                                     msg=msg,
1526                                 )
1527                         except ValueError:
1528                             # This should only happen when deprecated_alias['date'] is not in ISO format. Since
1529                             # schema validation already reported this as an error, don't report it a second
1530                             # time.
1531                             pass
1532 
1533             has_version = False
1534             if self.collection and self.collection_version is not None:
1535                 compare_version = self.collection_version
1536                 version_of_what = "this collection (%s)" % self.collection_version_str
1537                 code_prefix = 'collection'
1538                 has_version = True
1539             elif not self.collection:
1540                 compare_version = LOOSE_ANSIBLE_VERSION
1541                 version_of_what = "Ansible (%s)" % ansible_version
1542                 code_prefix = 'ansible'
1543                 has_version = True
1544 
1545             removed_in_version = data.get('removed_in_version', None)
1546             if removed_in_version is not None:
1547                 try:
1548                     collection_name = data.get('removed_from_collection')
1549                     removed_in = self._create_version(str(removed_in_version), collection_name=collection_name)
1550                     if has_version and collection_name == self.collection_name and compare_version >= removed_in:
1551                         msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1552                         if context:
1553                             msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1554                         msg += " has a deprecated removed_in_version %r," % removed_in_version
1555                         msg += " i.e. the version is less than or equal to the current version of %s" % version_of_what
1556                         self.reporter.error(
1557                             path=self.object_path,
1558                             code=code_prefix + '-deprecated-version',
1559                             msg=msg,
1560                         )
1561                 except ValueError as e:
1562                     msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1563                     if context:
1564                         msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1565                     msg += " has an invalid removed_in_version number %r: %s" % (removed_in_version, e)
1566                     self.reporter.error(
1567                         path=self.object_path,
1568                         code='invalid-deprecated-version',
1569                         msg=msg,
1570                     )
1571                 except TypeError:
1572                     msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1573                     if context:
1574                         msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1575                     msg += " has an invalid removed_in_version number %r: " % (removed_in_version, )
1576                     msg += " error while comparing to version of %s" % version_of_what
1577                     self.reporter.error(
1578                         path=self.object_path,
1579                         code='invalid-deprecated-version',
1580                         msg=msg,
1581                     )
1582 
1583             if deprecated_aliases is not None:
1584                 for deprecated_alias in deprecated_aliases:
1585                     if 'name' in deprecated_alias and 'version' in deprecated_alias:
1586                         try:
1587                             collection_name = deprecated_alias.get('collection_name')
1588                             version = self._create_version(str(deprecated_alias['version']), collection_name=collection_name)
1589                             if has_version and collection_name == self.collection_name and compare_version >= version:
1590                                 msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1591                                 if context:
1592                                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1593                                 msg += " has deprecated aliases '%s' with removal in version %r," % (
1594                                     deprecated_alias['name'], deprecated_alias['version'])
1595                                 msg += " i.e. the version is less than or equal to the current version of %s" % version_of_what
1596                                 self.reporter.error(
1597                                     path=self.object_path,
1598                                     code=code_prefix + '-deprecated-version',
1599                                     msg=msg,
1600                                 )
1601                         except ValueError as e:
1602                             msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1603                             if context:
1604                                 msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1605                             msg += " has deprecated aliases '%s' with invalid removal version %r: %s" % (
1606                                 deprecated_alias['name'], deprecated_alias['version'], e)
1607                             self.reporter.error(
1608                                 path=self.object_path,
1609                                 code='invalid-deprecated-version',
1610                                 msg=msg,
1611                             )
1612                         except TypeError:
1613                             msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1614                             if context:
1615                                 msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1616                             msg += " has deprecated aliases '%s' with invalid removal version %r:" % (
1617                                 deprecated_alias['name'], deprecated_alias['version'])
1618                             msg += " error while comparing to version of %s" % version_of_what
1619                             self.reporter.error(
1620                                 path=self.object_path,
1621                                 code='invalid-deprecated-version',
1622                                 msg=msg,
1623                             )
1624 
1625             aliases = data.get('aliases', [])
1626             if arg in aliases:
1627                 msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1628                 if context:
1629                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1630                 msg += " is specified as its own alias"
1631                 self.reporter.error(
1632                     path=self.object_path,
1633                     code='parameter-alias-self',
1634                     msg=msg
1635                 )
1636             if len(aliases) > len(set(aliases)):
1637                 msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1638                 if context:
1639                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1640                 msg += " has at least one alias specified multiple times in aliases"
1641                 self.reporter.error(
1642                     path=self.object_path,
1643                     code='parameter-alias-repeated',
1644                     msg=msg
1645                 )
1646             if not context and arg == 'state':
1647                 bad_states = set(['list', 'info', 'get']) & set(data.get('choices', set()))
1648                 for bad_state in bad_states:
1649                     self.reporter.error(
1650                         path=self.object_path,
1651                         code='parameter-state-invalid-choice',
1652                         msg="Argument 'state' includes the value '%s' as a choice" % bad_state)
1653             if not data.get('removed_in_version', None) and not data.get('removed_at_date', None):
1654                 args_from_argspec.add(arg)
1655                 args_from_argspec.update(aliases)
1656             else:
1657                 deprecated_args_from_argspec.add(arg)
1658                 deprecated_args_from_argspec.update(aliases)
1659             if arg == 'provider' and self.object_path.startswith('lib/ansible/modules/network/'):
1660                 if data.get('options') is not None and not isinstance(data.get('options'), Mapping):
1661                     self.reporter.error(
1662                         path=self.object_path,
1663                         code='invalid-argument-spec-options',
1664                         msg="Argument 'options' in argument_spec['provider'] must be a dictionary/hash when used",
1665                     )
1666                 elif data.get('options'):
1667                     # Record provider options from network modules, for later comparison
1668                     for provider_arg, provider_data in data.get('options', {}).items():
1669                         provider_args.add(provider_arg)
1670                         provider_args.update(provider_data.get('aliases', []))
1671 
1672             if data.get('required') and data.get('default', object) != object:
1673                 msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1674                 if context:
1675                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1676                 msg += " is marked as required but specifies a default. Arguments with a" \
1677                        " default should not be marked as required"
1678                 self.reporter.error(
1679                     path=self.object_path,
1680                     code='no-default-for-required-parameter',
1681                     msg=msg
1682                 )
1683 
1684             if arg in provider_args:
1685                 # Provider args are being removed from network module top level
1686                 # don't validate docs<->arg_spec checks below
1687                 continue
1688 
1689             _type = data.get('type', 'str')
1690             if callable(_type):
1691                 _type_checker = _type
1692             else:
1693                 _type_checker = module._CHECK_ARGUMENT_TYPES_DISPATCHER.get(_type)
1694 
1695             _elements = data.get('elements')
1696             if (_type == 'list') and not _elements:
1697                 msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1698                 if context:
1699                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1700                 msg += " defines type as list but elements is not defined"
1701                 self.reporter.error(
1702                     path=self.object_path,
1703                     code='parameter-list-no-elements',
1704                     msg=msg
1705                 )
1706             if _elements:
1707                 if not callable(_elements):
1708                     module._CHECK_ARGUMENT_TYPES_DISPATCHER.get(_elements)
1709                 if _type != 'list':
1710                     msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1711                     if context:
1712                         msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1713                     msg += " defines elements as %s but it is valid only when value of parameter type is list" % _elements
1714                     self.reporter.error(
1715                         path=self.object_path,
1716                         code='parameter-invalid-elements',
1717                         msg=msg
1718                     )
1719 
1720             arg_default = None
1721             if 'default' in data and not is_empty(data['default']):
1722                 try:
1723                     with CaptureStd():
1724                         arg_default = _type_checker(data['default'])
1725                 except (Exception, SystemExit):
1726                     msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1727                     if context:
1728                         msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1729                     msg += " defines default as (%r) but this is incompatible with parameter type %r" % (data['default'], _type)
1730                     self.reporter.error(
1731                         path=self.object_path,
1732                         code='incompatible-default-type',
1733                         msg=msg
1734                     )
1735                     continue
1736             elif data.get('default') is None and _type == 'bool' and 'options' not in data:
1737                 arg_default = False
1738 
1739             doc_options_args = []
1740             for alias in sorted(set([arg] + list(aliases))):
1741                 if alias in doc_options:
1742                     doc_options_args.append(alias)
1743             if len(doc_options_args) == 0:
1744                 # Undocumented arguments will be handled later (search for undocumented-parameter)
1745                 doc_options_arg = {}
1746             else:
1747                 doc_options_arg = doc_options[doc_options_args[0]]
1748                 if len(doc_options_args) > 1:
1749                     msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1750                     if context:
1751                         msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1752                     msg += " with aliases %s is documented multiple times, namely as %s" % (
1753                         ", ".join([("'%s'" % alias) for alias in aliases]),
1754                         ", ".join([("'%s'" % alias) for alias in doc_options_args])
1755                     )
1756                     self.reporter.error(
1757                         path=self.object_path,
1758                         code='parameter-documented-multiple-times',
1759                         msg=msg
1760                     )
1761 
1762             try:
1763                 doc_default = None
1764                 if 'default' in doc_options_arg and not is_empty(doc_options_arg['default']):
1765                     with CaptureStd():
1766                         doc_default = _type_checker(doc_options_arg['default'])
1767                 elif doc_options_arg.get('default') is None and _type == 'bool' and 'suboptions' not in doc_options_arg:
1768                     doc_default = False
1769             except (Exception, SystemExit):
1770                 msg = "Argument '%s' in documentation" % arg
1771                 if context:
1772                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1773                 msg += " defines default as (%r) but this is incompatible with parameter type %r" % (doc_options_arg.get('default'), _type)
1774                 self.reporter.error(
1775                     path=self.object_path,
1776                     code='doc-default-incompatible-type',
1777                     msg=msg
1778                 )
1779                 continue
1780 
1781             if arg_default != doc_default:
1782                 msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1783                 if context:
1784                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1785                 msg += " defines default as (%r) but documentation defines default as (%r)" % (arg_default, doc_default)
1786                 self.reporter.error(
1787                     path=self.object_path,
1788                     code='doc-default-does-not-match-spec',
1789                     msg=msg
1790                 )
1791 
1792             doc_type = doc_options_arg.get('type')
1793             if 'type' in data and data['type'] is not None:
1794                 if doc_type is None:
1795                     if not arg.startswith('_'):  # hidden parameter, for example _raw_params
1796                         msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1797                         if context:
1798                             msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1799                         msg += " defines type as %r but documentation doesn't define type" % (data['type'])
1800                         self.reporter.error(
1801                             path=self.object_path,
1802                             code='parameter-type-not-in-doc',
1803                             msg=msg
1804                         )
1805                 elif data['type'] != doc_type:
1806                     msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1807                     if context:
1808                         msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1809                     msg += " defines type as %r but documentation defines type as %r" % (data['type'], doc_type)
1810                     self.reporter.error(
1811                         path=self.object_path,
1812                         code='doc-type-does-not-match-spec',
1813                         msg=msg
1814                     )
1815             else:
1816                 if doc_type is None:
1817                     msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1818                     if context:
1819                         msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1820                     msg += " uses default type ('str') but documentation doesn't define type"
1821                     self.reporter.error(
1822                         path=self.object_path,
1823                         code='doc-missing-type',
1824                         msg=msg
1825                     )
1826                 elif doc_type != 'str':
1827                     msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1828                     if context:
1829                         msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1830                     msg += " implies type as 'str' but documentation defines as %r" % doc_type
1831                     self.reporter.error(
1832                         path=self.object_path,
1833                         code='implied-parameter-type-mismatch',
1834                         msg=msg
1835                     )
1836 
1837             doc_choices = []
1838             try:
1839                 for choice in doc_options_arg.get('choices', []):
1840                     try:
1841                         with CaptureStd():
1842                             doc_choices.append(_type_checker(choice))
1843                     except (Exception, SystemExit):
1844                         msg = "Argument '%s' in documentation" % arg
1845                         if context:
1846                             msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1847                         msg += " defines choices as (%r) but this is incompatible with argument type %r" % (choice, _type)
1848                         self.reporter.error(
1849                             path=self.object_path,
1850                             code='doc-choices-incompatible-type',
1851                             msg=msg
1852                         )
1853                         raise StopIteration()
1854             except StopIteration:
1855                 continue
1856 
1857             arg_choices = []
1858             try:
1859                 for choice in data.get('choices', []):
1860                     try:
1861                         with CaptureStd():
1862                             arg_choices.append(_type_checker(choice))
1863                     except (Exception, SystemExit):
1864                         msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1865                         if context:
1866                             msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1867                         msg += " defines choices as (%r) but this is incompatible with argument type %r" % (choice, _type)
1868                         self.reporter.error(
1869                             path=self.object_path,
1870                             code='incompatible-choices',
1871                             msg=msg
1872                         )
1873                         raise StopIteration()
1874             except StopIteration:
1875                 continue
1876 
1877             if not compare_unordered_lists(arg_choices, doc_choices):
1878                 msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1879                 if context:
1880                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1881                 msg += " defines choices as (%r) but documentation defines choices as (%r)" % (arg_choices, doc_choices)
1882                 self.reporter.error(
1883                     path=self.object_path,
1884                     code='doc-choices-do-not-match-spec',
1885                     msg=msg
1886                 )
1887 
1888             doc_required = doc_options_arg.get('required', False)
1889             data_required = data.get('required', False)
1890             if (doc_required or data_required) and not (doc_required and data_required):
1891                 msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1892                 if context:
1893                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1894                 if doc_required:
1895                     msg += " is not required, but is documented as being required"
1896                 else:
1897                     msg += " is required, but is not documented as being required"
1898                 self.reporter.error(
1899                     path=self.object_path,
1900                     code='doc-required-mismatch',
1901                     msg=msg
1902                 )
1903 
1904             doc_elements = doc_options_arg.get('elements', None)
1905             doc_type = doc_options_arg.get('type', 'str')
1906             data_elements = data.get('elements', None)
1907             if (doc_elements and not doc_type == 'list'):
1908                 msg = "Argument '%s " % arg
1909                 if context:
1910                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1911                 msg += " defines parameter elements as %s but it is valid only when value of parameter type is list" % doc_elements
1912                 self.reporter.error(
1913                     path=self.object_path,
1914                     code='doc-elements-invalid',
1915                     msg=msg
1916                 )
1917             if (doc_elements or data_elements) and not (doc_elements == data_elements):
1918                 msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1919                 if context:
1920                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1921                 if data_elements:
1922                     msg += " specifies elements as %s," % data_elements
1923                 else:
1924                     msg += " does not specify elements,"
1925                 if doc_elements:
1926                     msg += "but elements is documented as being %s" % doc_elements
1927                 else:
1928                     msg += "but elements is not documented"
1929                 self.reporter.error(
1930                     path=self.object_path,
1931                     code='doc-elements-mismatch',
1932                     msg=msg
1933                 )
1934 
1935             spec_suboptions = data.get('options')
1936             doc_suboptions = doc_options_arg.get('suboptions', {})
1937             if spec_suboptions:
1938                 if not doc_suboptions:
1939                     msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1940                     if context:
1941                         msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1942                     msg += " has sub-options but documentation does not define it"
1943                     self.reporter.error(
1944                         path=self.object_path,
1945                         code='missing-suboption-docs',
1946                         msg=msg
1947                     )
1948                 self._validate_argument_spec({'options': doc_suboptions}, spec_suboptions, kwargs,
1949                                              context=context + [arg], last_context_spec=data)
1950 
1951         for arg in args_from_argspec:
1952             if not str(arg).isidentifier():
1953                 msg = "Argument '%s' in argument_spec" % arg
1954                 if context:
1955                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1956                 msg += " is not a valid python identifier"
1957                 self.reporter.error(
1958                     path=self.object_path,
1959                     code='parameter-invalid',
1960                     msg=msg
1961                 )
1962 
1963         if docs:
1964             args_from_docs = set()
1965             for arg, data in doc_options.items():
1966                 args_from_docs.add(arg)
1967                 args_from_docs.update(data.get('aliases', []))
1968 
1969             args_missing_from_docs = args_from_argspec.difference(args_from_docs)
1970             docs_missing_from_args = args_from_docs.difference(args_from_argspec | deprecated_args_from_argspec)
1971             for arg in args_missing_from_docs:
1972                 if arg in provider_args:
1973                     # Provider args are being removed from network module top level
1974                     # So they are likely not documented on purpose
1975                     continue
1976                 msg = "Argument '%s'" % arg
1977                 if context:
1978                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1979                 msg += " is listed in the argument_spec, but not documented in the module documentation"
1980                 self.reporter.error(
1981                     path=self.object_path,
1982                     code='undocumented-parameter',
1983                     msg=msg
1984                 )
1985             for arg in docs_missing_from_args:
1986                 msg = "Argument '%s'" % arg
1987                 if context:
1988                     msg += " found in %s" % " -> ".join(context)
1989                 msg += " is listed in DOCUMENTATION.options, but not accepted by the module argument_spec"
1990                 self.reporter.error(
1991                     path=self.object_path,
1992                     code='nonexistent-parameter-documented',
1993                     msg=msg
1994                 )

1996     def _check_for_new_args(self, doc):
1997         if not self.base_branch or self._is_new_module():
1998             return
1999 
2000         with CaptureStd():
2001             try:
2002                 existing_doc, dummy_examples, dummy_return, existing_metadata = get_docstring(
2003                     self.base_module, fragment_loader, verbose=True, collection_name=self.collection_name, is_module=True)
2004                 existing_options = existing_doc.get('options', {}) or {}
2005             except AssertionError:
2006                 fragment = doc['extends_documentation_fragment']
2007                 self.reporter.warning(
2008                     path=self.object_path,
2009                     code='missing-existing-doc-fragment',
2010                     msg='Pre-existing DOCUMENTATION fragment missing: %s' % fragment
2011                 )
2012                 return
2013             except Exception as e:
2014                 self.reporter.warning_trace(
2015                     path=self.object_path,
2016                     tracebk=e
2017                 )
2018                 self.reporter.warning(
2019                     path=self.object_path,
2020                     code='unknown-doc-fragment',
2021                     msg=('Unknown pre-existing DOCUMENTATION error, see TRACE. Submodule refs may need updated')
2022                 )
2023                 return
2024 
2025         try:
2026             mod_collection_name = existing_doc.get('version_added_collection')
2027             mod_version_added = self._create_strict_version(
2028                 str(existing_doc.get('version_added', '0.0')),
2029                 collection_name=mod_collection_name)
2030         except ValueError:
2031             mod_collection_name = self.collection_name
2032             mod_version_added = self._create_strict_version('0.0')
2033 
2034         options = doc.get('options', {}) or {}
2035 
2036         should_be = '.'.join(ansible_version.split('.')[:2])
2037         strict_ansible_version = self._create_strict_version(should_be, collection_name='ansible.builtin')
2038 
2039         for option, details in options.items():
2040             try:
2041                 names = [option] + details.get('aliases', [])
2042             except (TypeError, AttributeError):
2043                 # Reporting of this syntax error will be handled by schema validation.
2044                 continue
2045 
2046             if any(name in existing_options for name in names):
2047                 # The option already existed. Make sure version_added didn't change.
2048                 for name in names:
2049                     existing_collection_name = existing_options.get(name, {}).get('version_added_collection')
2050                     existing_version = existing_options.get(name, {}).get('version_added')
2051                     if existing_version:
2052                         break
2053                 current_collection_name = details.get('version_added_collection')
2054                 current_version = details.get('version_added')
2055                 if current_collection_name != existing_collection_name:
2056                     self.reporter.error(
2057                         path=self.object_path,
2058                         code='option-incorrect-version-added-collection',
2059                         msg=('version_added for existing option (%s) should '
2060                              'belong to collection %r. Currently belongs to %r' %
2061                              (option, current_collection_name, existing_collection_name))
2062                     )
2063                 elif str(current_version) != str(existing_version):
2064                     self.reporter.error(
2065                         path=self.object_path,
2066                         code='option-incorrect-version-added',
2067                         msg=('version_added for existing option (%s) should '
2068                              'be %r. Currently %r' %
2069                              (option, existing_version, current_version))
2070                     )
2071                 continue
2072 
2073             try:
2074                 collection_name = details.get('version_added_collection')
2075                 version_added = self._create_strict_version(
2076                     str(details.get('version_added', '0.0')),
2077                     collection_name=collection_name)
2078             except ValueError as e:
2079                 self.reporter.error(
2080                     path=self.object_path,
2081                     code='option-invalid-version-added',
2082                     msg=('version_added for option (%s) is not a valid '
2083                          'version for %s. Currently %r. Error: %s' %
2084                          (option, collection_name, details.get('version_added', '0.0'), e))
2085                 )
2086                 continue
2087 
2088             if collection_name != self.collection_name:
2089                 continue
2090             if (strict_ansible_version != mod_version_added and
2091                     (version_added < strict_ansible_version or
2092                      strict_ansible_version < version_added)):
2093                 self.reporter.error(
2094                     path=self.object_path,
2095                     code='option-incorrect-version-added',
2096                     msg=('version_added for new option (%s) should '
2097                          'be %r. Currently %r' %
2098                          (option, should_be, version_added))
2099                 )
2100 
2101         return existing_doc

2103     @staticmethod
2104     def is_blacklisted(path):
2105         base_name = os.path.basename(path)
2106         file_name = os.path.splitext(base_name)[0]
2107 
2108         if file_name.startswith('_') and os.path.islink(path):
2109             return True
2110 
2111         if not frozenset((base_name, file_name)).isdisjoint(ModuleValidator.BLACKLIST):
2112             return True
2113 
2114         for pat in ModuleValidator.BLACKLIST_PATTERNS:
2115             if fnmatch(base_name, pat):
2116                 return True
2117 
2118         return False

2120     def validate(self):
2121         super(ModuleValidator, self).validate()
2122         if not self._python_module() and not self._powershell_module():
2123             self.reporter.error(
2124                 path=self.object_path,
2125                 code='invalid-extension',
2126                 msg=('Official Ansible modules must have a .py '
2127                      'extension for python modules or a .ps1 '
2128                      'for powershell modules')
2129             )
2130             self._python_module_override = True
2131 
2132         if self._python_module() and self.ast is None:
2133             self.reporter.error(
2134                 path=self.object_path,
2135                 code='python-syntax-error',
2136                 msg='Python SyntaxError while parsing module'
2137             )
2138             try:
2139                 compile(self.text, self.path, 'exec')
2140             except Exception:
2141                 self.reporter.trace(
2142                     path=self.object_path,
2143                     tracebk=traceback.format_exc()
2144                 )
2145             return
2146 
2147         end_of_deprecation_should_be_removed_only = False
2148         if self._python_module():
2149             doc_info, docs = self._validate_docs()
2150 
2151             # See if current version => deprecated.removed_in, ie, should be docs only
2152             if docs and docs.get('deprecated', False):
2153 
2154                 if 'removed_in' in docs['deprecated']:
2155                     removed_in = None
2156                     collection_name = docs['deprecated'].get('removed_from_collection')
2157                     version = docs['deprecated']['removed_in']
2158                     if collection_name != self.collection_name:
2159                         self.reporter.error(
2160                             path=self.object_path,
2161                             code='invalid-module-deprecation-source',
2162                             msg=('The deprecation version for a module must be added in this collection')
2163                         )
2164                     else:
2165                         try:
2166                             removed_in = self._create_strict_version(str(version), collection_name=collection_name)
2167                         except ValueError as e:
2168                             self.reporter.error(
2169                                 path=self.object_path,
2170                                 code='invalid-module-deprecation-version',
2171                                 msg=('The deprecation version %r cannot be parsed: %s' % (version, e))
2172                             )
2173 
2174                     if removed_in:
2175                         if not self.collection:
2176                             strict_ansible_version = self._create_strict_version(
2177                                 '.'.join(ansible_version.split('.')[:2]), self.collection_name)
2178                             end_of_deprecation_should_be_removed_only = strict_ansible_version >= removed_in
2179                         elif self.collection_version:
2180                             strict_ansible_version = self.collection_version
2181                             end_of_deprecation_should_be_removed_only = strict_ansible_version >= removed_in
2182 
2183                 # handle deprecation by date
2184                 if 'removed_at_date' in docs['deprecated']:
2185                     try:
2186                         removed_at_date = docs['deprecated']['removed_at_date']
2187                         if parse_isodate(removed_at_date, allow_date=True) < datetime.date.today():
2188                             msg = "Module's deprecated.removed_at_date date '%s' is before today" % removed_at_date
2189                             self.reporter.error(path=self.object_path, code='deprecated-date', msg=msg)
2190                     except ValueError:
2191                         # This happens if the date cannot be parsed. This is already checked by the schema.
2192                         pass
2193 
2194         if self._python_module() and not self._just_docs() and not end_of_deprecation_should_be_removed_only:
2195             self._validate_ansible_module_call(docs)
2196             self._check_for_sys_exit()
2197             self._find_blacklist_imports()
2198             main = self._find_main_call()
2199             self._find_module_utils(main)
2200             self._find_has_import()
2201             first_callable = self._get_first_callable()
2202             self._ensure_imports_below_docs(doc_info, first_callable)
2203             self._check_for_subprocess()
2204             self._check_for_os_call()
2205 
2206         if self._powershell_module():
2207             if self.basename in self.PS_DOC_BLACKLIST:
2208                 return
2209 
2210             self._validate_ps_replacers()
2211             docs_path = self._find_ps_docs_py_file()
2212 
2213             # We can only validate PowerShell arg spec if it is using the new Ansible.Basic.AnsibleModule util
2214             pattern = r'(?im)^#\s*ansiblerequires\s+\-csharputil\s*Ansible\.Basic'
2215             if re.search(pattern, self.text) and self.object_name not in self.PS_ARG_VALIDATE_BLACKLIST:
2216                 with ModuleValidator(docs_path, base_branch=self.base_branch, git_cache=self.git_cache) as docs_mv:
2217                     docs = docs_mv._validate_docs()[1]
2218                     self._validate_ansible_module_call(docs)
2219 
2220         self._check_gpl3_header()
2221         if not self._just_docs() and not end_of_deprecation_should_be_removed_only:
2222             self._check_interpreter(powershell=self._powershell_module())
2223             self._check_type_instead_of_isinstance(
2224                 powershell=self._powershell_module()
2225             )
2226         if end_of_deprecation_should_be_removed_only:
2227             # Ensure that `if __name__ == '__main__':` calls `removed_module()` which ensure that the module has no code in
2228             main = self._find_main_call('removed_module')
2229             # FIXME: Ensure that the version in the call to removed_module is less than +2.
2230             # Otherwise it's time to remove the file (This may need to be done in another test to
2231             # avoid breaking whenever the Ansible version bumps)

2271 def re_compile(value):
2272     """
2273     Argparse expects things to raise TypeError, re.compile raises an re.error
2274     exception
2275 
2276     This function is a shorthand to convert the re.error exception to a
2277     TypeError
2278     """
2279 
2280     try:
2281         return re.compile(value)
2282     except re.error as e:
2283         raise TypeError(e)

2371     if not args.collection:
2372         for path in sorted(check_dirs):
2373             pv = PythonPackageValidator(path, reporter=reporter)
2374             pv.validate()
2375 
2376     if args.format == 'plain':
2377         sys.exit(reporter.plain(warnings=args.warnings, output=args.output))
2378     else:
2379         sys.exit(reporter.json(warnings=args.warnings, output=args.output))

2382 class GitCache:
2383     def __init__(self, base_branch):
2384         self.base_branch = base_branch
2385 
2386         if self.base_branch:
2387             self.base_tree = self._git(['ls-tree', '-r', '--name-only', self.base_branch, 'lib/ansible/modules/'])
2388         else:
2389             self.base_tree = []
2390 
2391         try:
2392             self.head_tree = self._git(['ls-tree', '-r', '--name-only', 'HEAD', 'lib/ansible/modules/'])
2393         except GitError as ex:
2394             if ex.status == 128:
2395                 # fallback when there is no .git directory
2396                 self.head_tree = self._get_module_files()
2397             else:
2398                 raise
2399         except OSError as ex:
2400             if ex.errno == errno.ENOENT:
2401                 # fallback when git is not installed
2402                 self.head_tree = self._get_module_files()
2403             else:
2404                 raise
2405 
2406         self.base_module_paths = dict((os.path.basename(p), p) for p in self.base_tree if os.path.splitext(p)[1] in ('.py', '.ps1'))
2407 
2408         self.base_module_paths.pop('__init__.py', None)
2409 
2410         self.head_aliased_modules = set()
2411 
2412         for path in self.head_tree:
2413             filename = os.path.basename(path)
2414 
2415             if filename.startswith('_') and filename != '__init__.py':
2416                 if os.path.islink(path):
2417                     self.head_aliased_modules.add(os.path.basename(os.path.realpath(path)))
2418 
2419     @staticmethod
2420     def _get_module_files():
2421         module_files = []
2422 
2423         for (dir_path, dir_names, file_names) in os.walk('lib/ansible/modules/'):
2424             for file_name in file_names:
2425                 module_files.append(os.path.join(dir_path, file_name))
2426 
2427         return module_files
2428 
2429     @staticmethod
2430     def _git(args):
2431         cmd = ['git'] + args
2432         p = subprocess.Popen(cmd, stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.PIPE)
2433         stdout, stderr = p.communicate()
2434         if p.returncode != 0:
2435             raise GitError(stderr, p.returncode)
2436         return stdout.decode('utf-8').splitlines()

2439 class GitError(Exception):
2440     def __init__(self, message, status):
2441         super(GitError, self).__init__(message)
2442 
2443         self.status = status
